  "texts": [
    "Then, TSV-Merge computes SVD of every layer-wise task vector,",
    "where the singular vectors U (ℓ) i and V",
    "(ℓ) i are called Task Singular Vectors (TSVs) and the diagonal entries of Σ (ℓ) i quantify their importance.",
    "TSV-Merge then retains only the top 1 T fraction of singular components for each (i, ℓ) to control capacity and suppress noise, keeping the highest-energy directions.",
    "Then, the truncated TSVs are aggregated (suppressing ℓ for brevity) by concatenation,"
  ],
